<subSubSection pageNumber="682" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="682">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="682">Note:</emphasis>
Wallace (1975) evidently regarded material in LINN as the type while Wilbur &amp; Luteyn (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="682">Ann. Missouri Bot. Gard.</emphasis>
65: 102. 1978) indicated 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="682">Clayton 245</emphasis>
(BM), which they had not seen and believed to be instead at LINN, as type. Reveal &amp; al. (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="682">Huntia</emphasis>
7: 228. 1987) provided a detailed review, concluding that the Kalm specimen in LINN should be the type.
</paragraph>
